{
  "texts": [
    "They also proved the converse statement that every flat k-chain is a metric current.",
    "Later, the theory of metric currents was extended by Lang to include currents not of finite mass and an analogous conjecture was stated for this type of currents.",
    "To be explicit, Lang conjectures [30, page 716] that every compactly supported metrick-current in R d is a flat k-chain.",
    "We shall abbreviate this conjecture to FCC(L)[k, d].",
    "It is obvious that FCC(L)[k, d] implies FCC(AK)[k, d] for anyk and d. This implication, in light of our results, is not very useful.It appears that no results concerning FCC(L) [k, d] are available in the literature other than the description of the problem itself due to Lang."
  ]
}